  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Software Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Position Summary</strong></p><p>This is an entry-level position designed for fresh graduates or early-career engineers. As a Junior Software Engineer, you will focus on building a strong technical foundation under the mentorship of senior staff. Your primary goal is to learn the Alpha X technology stack, assist in code development, and support the team during on-site deployments in the manufacturing sector.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in developing and testing software components according to strict technical specifications and Object-Oriented principles</li><li>Rapidly acquire skills in new programming languages and tools to meet changing project requirements.</li><li>Accompany senior engineers to client sites (local and regional) to support software installation, customization, enhancement and testing.</li><li>Prepare basic technical documentation and help logs for developed modules.</li><li>Perform any ad-hoc duties assigned by the Company as and when required.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications & Skills</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Strong academic understanding of <strong>Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)</strong>.</li><li>Willingness and ability to learn new programming languages quickly.</li><li>Willingness to travel and work on-site at client factories.</li><li>Professional fluency in English (written and spoken)</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Preferred/ Additional</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of <strong>Java</strong> or <strong>Go-lang, SECS and GEM</strong> are added advantage.</li><li>Ability to communicate in Mandarin or Malay is an added advantage for regional\ncoordination.</li><li>Basic understanding of <strong>Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES) </strong>or industrial concepts.                                                                  </li></ul>",
